Schwehr: Can you repeat
the question?

00:20:24.767 --> 00:20:30.701
man: [indistinct]

00:20:32.634 --> 00:20:34.801
Schwehr: We would rather have
Google do that than us, yes.

00:20:34.801 --> 00:20:37.267
It would be great
to have a street-view car,

00:20:37.267 --> 00:20:39.567
that we plunk on top of a ship,
and drive around the harbor.

00:20:39.567 --> 00:20:43.734
We're in a way emulating that,
except for one aspect.

00:20:43.734 --> 00:20:45.701
In street view,
you want to show everything,

00:20:45.701 --> 00:20:48.834
because people are interested in
all sorts of different features.

00:20:48.834 --> 00:20:51.033
Here, we have a community
that actually wants you

00:20:51.033 --> 00:20:52.434
to go in
and decimate the data,

00:20:52.434 --> 00:20:54.100
and just find
those key features.

00:20:54.100 --> 00:20:55.634
So when they're coming
into a harbor,

00:20:55.634 --> 00:20:58.067
they don't want to know every
nook and cranny of the harbor,

00:20:58.067 --> 00:21:00.100
they want to know the key
lighthouses, the buildings,

00:21:00.100 --> 00:21:03.868
the features they need
to go to where they're going.

00:21:03.868 --> 00:21:05.200
So they're going
to aim for that lighthouse,

00:21:05.200 --> 00:21:08.100
take a left at the third pier
and head for home.

00:21:08.100 --> 00:21:09.901
And it may be foggy and dark.

00:21:09.901 --> 00:21:11.734
So they want
to have that best knowledge

00:21:11.734 --> 00:21:14.200
without all of the street view
like stuff in there.

00:21:14.200 --> 00:21:16.267
So we have an
extra decimation problem.

